": "f5f1fd", "default": false, "description": "Category: This is a bug."}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 5, "created_at": "2018-05-23T19:49:53Z", "updated_at": "2023-03-13T13:23:50Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "https://github.com/rustwasm/rust_wasm_template has\r\n\r\n```toml\r\n[lib]\r\ncrate-type = [\r\n  # Build a cdylib to make a `.wasm` library.\r\n  \"cdylib\",\r\n  # Build an rlib for testing and benching.\r\n  \"rlib\"\r\n]\r\n\r\n[profile.release]\r\nlto = true\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe `lto = true` is ignored for everything because rlibs don't support LTO. I would expect that the cdylib has LTO and that only the rlib ignores the LTO options.\r\n\r\n@alexcrichton tells me this is a rust compiler bug, not a cargo bug.\r\n\r\nFWIW, this command does not work either:\r\n\r\n```\r\ncargo rustc -- -C lto=fat --crate-type cdylib\r\n```", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/51009/reactions", "total_count": 9, "+1": 9, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/51009/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}